      "id": "RQ-0011",
      "status": "done",
      "title": "Automate the missing-agent-browser error-path contract",
      "description": "Principles violated: F) Fail fast, H) Operational hygiene, J) Consistency/Integrity.\n\nWhy it matters: the repo treats the missing-binary path as a minimum validation item and promises a specific user-facing error, but the normal automated gate does not exercise that ENOENT branch. A regression in the not-on-PATH behavior could therefore ship while `npm run verify` still passes.\n\nMinimal proposed fix: add a focused fake-binary or PATH-stripping test that forces the spawn `ENOENT` branch and asserts the user-facing error text plus `isError: true`. Keep the current typecheck/test/package verification entrypoints unchanged once the new coverage lands.",
      "priority": "medium",
      "tags": [
        "maintenance",
        "testing",
        "operability",
