        "package.json",
        "scripts"
      ],
      "evidence": [
        "path: docs/COMMAND_REFERENCE.md :: Upstream baseline :: the command reference is explicitly pinned to `agent-browser 0.26.0` and repeats that version in the heading text",
        "path: scripts/verify-command-reference.mjs :: EXPECTED_VERSION and token lists :: the verifier hardcodes the target version and a large manual set of required documentation and upstream-help tokens",
        "path: test/verify-command-reference.test.ts :: fakeRunWithVersion :: tests duplicate the pinned version assumption and verifier expectations"
      ],
      "plan": [
        "Design a single canonical metadata source for the targeted upstream version and expected capability tokens, including how generated doc fragments are marked.",
        "Refactor the command-reference verifier and any generated doc fragments to consume that metadata instead of duplicating constants.",
        "Update tests to validate the metadata-driven flow rather than hardcoded scattered version assumptions.",
        "Document the maintainer workflow for bumping the targeted upstream version and regenerating derived content, including the no-manual-edit rule for generated fragments.",
        "Verify by updating the metadata source in a controlled test scenario and confirming the verifier, docs, and tests all change coherently from that one source."
