      "title": "Surface actionable confirm and deny recovery flows",
      "description": "Opportunity type: reliability. The tracked upstream surface includes guarded-action confirmation primitives such as `confirm <id>`, `deny <id>`, and `--confirm-actions`, but the wrapper does not yet make pending confirmations feel actionable inside Pi. Right now an agent can discover the command family in docs, but not through a first-class recovery experience. Why it matters: guarded actions are a safety feature, and the native tool should help agents finish those flows correctly instead of dropping them into generic details blobs. Proposed approach: after capturing the upstream confirmation-needed result shape, detect confirmation-needed outputs, render the pending action id and next-step commands clearly, and add docs and tests for approval and denial recovery. Risks and mitigations: keep the wrapper thin by surfacing upstream ids and next calls rather than inventing a second confirmation model, and preserve redaction for sensitive action context. Acceptance criteria: pending confirmation results are rendered with the id and follow-up examples, the wrapper keeps redaction intact for sensitive confirmation contexts, and tests cover both confirm and deny paths.",
